        Db::table('actors')->insert([
            'name' => 'Eva Bourne',
            'dob' => null,
            'bio' => 'Eva Bourne grew up in the East Kootenays of British Columbia in the town of Creston. Eva\'s creativity was consistently encouraged by a loving mother and father of eccentric nature. Eva moved to Cranbrook B.C. after high school and began a Dental Assisting program, though she quickly realized her passion was elsewhere. She daringly made the decision to drop out and to move to Vancouver to study acting. Shortly after moving to Vancouver, Eva booked her first role on USA Network\'s "Psych". A slew of opportunities followed; Eva\'s TV credits include guest starring roles on The CW\'s "Emily Owens M.D.", CTV\'s "Motive", and TNT\'s "Falling Skies". She had recurring roles on SyFy\'s "Caprica", Discovery\'s "R.L. Stine\'s The Haunting Hour", and most notably, on ABC\'s mega hit "Once Upon a Time" as Princess Eva. Eva has already experienced working with Hollywood elite. On the big screen, Eva has appeared in the feature films Words and Pictures with Clive Owen and Juliette Binoche, and in The Big Year with Steve Martin, Owen Wilson and Rosamund Pike.',
